│ instructions, which is where the crash occurs. This suggests that even though scheduling   │
│ failed for the operands (the `fcmp`s), the logic continues and attempts to process a       │
│ partially constructed (and likely inconsistent) state.                                     │
│                                                                                            │
│ ### 3. Root Cause Analysis                                                                 │
│                                                                                            │
│ The root cause lies in how `BoUpSLP::getEntryCost` handles the failure of `canSchedule`.   │
│                                                                                            │
│ 1.  The vectorizer identifies a bundle of `select` instructions to analyze.                │
│ 2.  It calls `getEntryCost` on this bundle. Inside `getEntryCost`, it tries to analyze the │
│ operands.                                                                                  │
│ 3.  One group of operands is the `fcmp` instructions. The vectorizer calls `canSchedule`   │
│ to check if these `fcmp` instructions can be vectorized and scheduled together.            │
